===============================================================================
Interoperability formats
===============================================================================

For data portability, this project implements importers and exporters
targeting publicly documented file formats used by Notion (and other
block-editor / note-taking products):

- Markdown (CommonMark + GFM extensions)
- CSV (RFC 4180)
- HTML (W3C)
- JSON (in shapes that mirror Notion's public API documentation
  available at https://developers.notion.com/, for the explicit
  purpose of enabling users to move their data between products)
- ZIP archives bundling the above

These adapters consume / produce **public, documented file formats
only**. Implementing such interoperability is a long-recognised fair-use
of trademark + format references — see, e.g., **Sega Enterprises Ltd.
v. Accolade, Inc.**, 977 F.2d 1510 (9th Cir. 1992) and
**Sony Computer Entertainment, Inc. v. Connectix Corp.**, 203 F.3d 596
(9th Cir. 2000) — both of which protect reverse-engineered
interoperability work.

